Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content:
ok I have tried to explain this before, maybe nobody understoof it or it got lost. 
WHY iguana breaks when you restart it is the KMD block exeption for AC. 
10 KMD blocks must hav past before an AC can be notarized. 
If your ndoe starts a round, that no other nodes start, how can it reach consensus for a ntoarization?

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: This is what the 0s mean.

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: you have started a dpow round, and not enough other ndoes did.

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: so it simply fails... its just how it works

Author: Strob#3417
Content: ok cool

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: best way to stop this happenign is to never restart ever...

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: or restart a few times, until it randoml;y enters a round correctly

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: WHEN you start, makes a lot of diffrence, but it is 100% luck
